The paper discusses the design of buffer managers and storage systems in database management systems, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Databases). The paper also mentions the use of non-volatile memory (NVM) technologies, which could be classified under cs.AR (Architecture), cs.OS (Operating Systems), and cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, the paper proposes techniques for optimizing the storage hierarchy and adapting to different workloads, which could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
